Moment of silence in memory of Alfredo Di Stefano
Together with the Argentina Football Association and Real Madrid, FIFA has decided that the global football community will pay tribute to Alfredo Di Stefano at today’s FIFA World Cup semi-final match between the national teams of the Netherlands and Argentina. 
A moment of silence will be held ahead of the match in memory of Di Stefano and a picture of him will be shown on the stadium’s giant screen. Furthermore, Argentina’s national team will wear black armbands. 
Di Stefano, one of the greatest players of all-time, passed away on Monday, 7 July, at the age of 88. 
